    &lt;Title&gt;All in all, a fantastic hospital experience.&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I am not good with hospitals, but Leigh infirmary just has something about it that feels somehow less like a hospital. It is spotless, calm, and the staff are really nice. I went for a colonoscopy and was extremely nervous but the whole experience was made manageable by the nursing staff and it went well. I will say I was first greeted by a nurse who seemed quite nervous, and almost a little too dramatic when reading the risks which made me nervous. She made a bit of a hash of finding a vein too, so it started badly, at one point she said "You arent going to faint on me are you?".... but we got there in the end.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
